      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KENSINGTON FLYER (3) jumped from an awkward draw but scored by 2.75 lengths (22.19) at Ballarat in Grade 5. Yet to fire here from three runs. Ran the fastest time on the program in his latest win. Looks the testing material. SHIMA BALLAD (1) was well back throughout but attacked the line strongly to place, 1.1 lengths from the winner (24.68) at Sale in Grade 5. Expecting another good run. MEMPHIS MACK (2) is a talented type and proved too classy last time to win by 0.8 lengths at this track in a handy 26.35 beating Pacific Lola. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card in scoring last start. Has hit winning form and can measure up again. WILD CUDDLE (6) should be thereabouts after filling a top-three spot most recently.",
